01:15.108 --> 01:18.114
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

01:18.114 --> 01:20.578
ABDI: [grunts]

01:20.578 --> 01:22.414
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:22.414 --> 01:25.505
[tape ripping]

01:25.505 --> 01:27.717
[dog snarling, barking]

01:27.717 --> 01:29.554
[Abdi panting]

01:29.554 --> 01:33.311
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:33.311 --> 01:35.566
[grunts]

01:35.566 --> 01:38.572
[barking continues]

01:41.912 --> 01:44.918
<i>[eerie music]</i>

01:44.918 --> 01:49.427
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:49.427 --> 01:51.807
[barking continues distantly]

01:51.807 --> 01:54.813
[engine humming]

01:58.278 --> 02:00.533
[gravel crunching,
brakes squeal]

02:00.533 --> 02:02.787
[engine stops]

02:02.787 --> 02:05.000
[door latch clicks]

02:05.000 --> 02:06.920
Guys, c‐‐can you help, please?

02:06.920 --> 02:08.757
NURSE: Yeah. Yeah.

02:08.757 --> 02:10.761
JAMAL: Yo, can we get
some help, please?

02:10.761 --> 02:12.306
NURSE: Where is he?

02:12.306 --> 02:14.561
[car creaks]

02:14.561 --> 02:16.815
Got him.
JAMAL: What happened?

02:16.815 --> 02:19.613
I got him,
I got him, I got him.

02:19.613 --> 02:21.867
Mr. Merrill?
Can you breathe?

02:21.867 --> 02:23.704
POP: [groans softly]
JAMAL: All right.

02:23.704 --> 02:26.752
NURSE: Watch your step.
Watch your step.

02:26.752 --> 02:29.048
<i>[music fades]</i>

02:58.314 --> 03:01.320
[keys jingling]

03:01.320 --> 03:04.326
<i>[tense ambient music]</i>

03:04.326 --> 03:10.213
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:10.213 --> 03:13.386
[keys jingling]

03:13.386 --> 03:20.400
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:21.570 --> 03:23.991
[car door slams]

03:35.931 --> 03:38.937
<i>[dark music]</i>

03:38.937 --> 03:45.951
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:55.721 --> 03:58.727
‐ [breathing heavily]

03:58.727 --> 04:05.741
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:07.327 --> 04:08.371
[shrieks]

04:08.371 --> 04:10.333
[beetles buzzing]

04:10.333 --> 04:13.297
[birds chirping]

04:16.011 --> 04:18.809
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:18.809 --> 04:20.478
[engine rumbling]

04:20.478 --> 04:22.149
[brakes squeal]

04:26.323 --> 04:33.337
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:37.972 --> 04:40.226
[leaves rustling]

04:40.226 --> 04:43.024
[crow calls]

04:43.024 --> 04:47.032
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:47.032 --> 04:50.038
[door creaking]

04:50.038 --> 04:52.250
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:52.250 --> 04:54.881
[door creaks shut]

04:54.881 --> 04:57.887
[wood creaking]

05:14.963 --> 05:17.300
[bird wings flutter]

05:20.014 --> 05:27.028
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:37.592 --> 05:40.180
[wings flutter]

05:40.180 --> 05:47.194
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:58.049 --> 06:01.055
[metal clattering,
wood creaking]

06:01.055 --> 06:02.934
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:02.934 --> 06:04.854
HASSAN: [speaking Somali]
‐ [gasps]

06:04.854 --> 06:07.860
<i>[sinister music]</i>

06:07.860 --> 06:12.452
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:12.452 --> 06:15.458
[shell crunching]

06:15.458 --> 06:20.928
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:20.928 --> 06:23.934
[breathing shakily]

06:23.934 --> 06:27.023
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:27.023 --> 06:30.405
‐ [speaking Somali sharply]

06:30.405 --> 06:33.704
[shouting in Somali]

06:38.254 --> 06:41.260
<i>[ominous music]</i>

06:41.260 --> 06:48.274
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:08.523 --> 07:11.529
<i>[foreboding music]</i>

07:11.529 --> 07:14.201
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:14.201 --> 07:17.207
[muffled indistinct chatter]

07:17.207 --> 07:18.668
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:18.668 --> 07:20.506
NADIA: Pop, take it easy.

07:20.506 --> 07:22.217
POP: What happened?

07:22.217 --> 07:24.806
‐ You've had a stroke‐‐
a mini one.

07:24.806 --> 07:26.601
‐ What?

07:26.601 --> 07:29.314
What happened?

07:29.314 --> 07:31.986
NADIA: I got this, Jamal.

07:31.986 --> 07:35.159
<i>[indistinct announcement</i>
<i>over PA]</i>

07:35.159 --> 07:37.998
[monitor beeping slowly]

07:37.998 --> 07:39.961
You tell me what happened.

07:39.961 --> 07:42.800
Do you remember‐‐
‐ What? What?

07:42.800 --> 07:44.344
What‐‐why‐‐

07:44.344 --> 07:45.889
NADIA: Abdi brought you here.

07:47.350 --> 07:49.522
I've been looking for him.

07:49.522 --> 07:52.945
He won't call me back.
‐ He should have left me there.

07:54.322 --> 07:57.203
I would have left me there.

07:57.203 --> 08:00.293
‐ Left you where?

08:00.293 --> 08:02.590
Pop?

08:02.590 --> 08:04.969
[indistinct chatter]

08:04.969 --> 08:07.307
POP: Did I hurt him?

08:07.307 --> 08:09.562
Is he okay?

08:09.562 --> 08:11.524
NADIA: What?

08:13.570 --> 08:16.116
Did you hurt Abdi?

08:16.116 --> 08:17.995
<i>[tense music]</i>

08:17.995 --> 08:20.709
‐ I‐‐I don't know.

08:20.709 --> 08:22.588
I don't know.

08:22.588 --> 08:24.299
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:24.299 --> 08:28.182
‐ What do you mean,
you don't know?

08:28.182 --> 08:30.228
[sighs]

08:30.228 --> 08:32.608
[retreating footsteps]

08:32.608 --> 08:35.404
Abdi, please call me.

08:35.404 --> 08:38.160
<i>[music fades]</i>

08:41.709 --> 08:44.715
[pencil scratching]

08:44.715 --> 08:47.345
[knocking on door]

08:52.105 --> 08:53.650
‐ Hey.

08:53.650 --> 08:55.779
Wanna go look for a dead guy?

08:55.779 --> 08:57.783
JOY: What?

09:02.585 --> 09:04.296
CHASE: [smacks lips]

09:04.296 --> 09:06.091
Is your mom here?

09:06.091 --> 09:09.180
JOY: She went to work.

09:09.180 --> 09:11.769
CHANCE: Love what you guys
haven't done with the place.

09:11.769 --> 09:13.355
‐ Yeah.

09:13.355 --> 09:15.861
‐ So, uh, dead guy.

09:15.861 --> 09:17.656
Sounds weird; hear me out.

09:17.656 --> 09:20.704
Ace Merrill‐‐you know,
the shitty landlord,
rapey‐eyes dude?

09:20.704 --> 09:22.625
They say he's dead.

09:22.625 --> 09:24.002
‐ Oh, my gosh.

09:24.002 --> 09:25.547
‐ It's fine.
He sucked.

09:25.547 --> 09:27.760
Anyway, we're gonna go
find the corpse.

09:27.760 --> 09:30.056
Usually dump them in the lake.

09:30.056 --> 09:32.936
Everything bad in this town
starts at Castle Lake.

09:32.936 --> 09:34.690
So are you in?

09:34.690 --> 09:36.527
It's gonna be a hike,
but I got snacks.

09:36.527 --> 09:37.988
Brownies.

09:37.988 --> 09:40.242
‐ Um, my mom‐‐

09:40.242 --> 09:42.246
um, I think I‐‐

09:42.246 --> 09:45.629
‐ You're fucking 16, right?

09:45.629 --> 09:48.677
‐ We're gonna be leaving town
like any second now.

09:49.887 --> 09:51.766
‐ Oh.

09:53.143 --> 09:55.607
Getting out of this shithole
already, huh?

09:57.820 --> 09:59.364
Keep the phone.

09:59.364 --> 10:02.579
Find a McDonald's somewhere
and hit me up.

10:05.000 --> 10:07.088
‐ Wait.

10:08.591 --> 10:10.094
I'll come with.

10:10.094 --> 10:11.889
CHANCE: Sweet.

10:11.889 --> 10:14.144
Bring a bathing suit.

10:15.354 --> 10:17.358
Or not.

10:18.903 --> 10:20.782
[door creaks, slams]

10:20.782 --> 10:23.788
<i>[The New Basement Tapes'</i>
<i>"Duncan and Jimmy"]</i>

10:23.788 --> 10:29.967
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:29.967 --> 10:32.221
[laughing]

10:32.221 --> 10:33.767
SINGER: ♪ And take your stand ♪

10:33.767 --> 10:37.440
♪ Tip your hat to the world ♪

10:37.440 --> 10:40.697
♪ Button up the bowtie
and dance all around ♪

10:40.697 --> 10:44.705
♪ Once again
with the fat Hawaiian girl ♪

10:44.705 --> 10:48.713
♪ Duncan and Jimmy
walk side by side ♪

10:48.713 --> 10:51.468
♪ Nobody walks between them ♪

10:51.468 --> 10:53.263
‐ Anchors aweigh.

10:53.263 --> 10:56.019
VERA: Well, if anyone sees
an old man's head bobbing,
that shit's mine.

10:56.019 --> 10:57.815
I call dibs.
‐ What?

10:57.815 --> 11:01.112
‐ Warden of Shawshank
86'd himself in this lake.

11:01.112 --> 11:03.743
They found the body
but not the head.

11:03.743 --> 11:05.204
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:05.204 --> 11:08.670
SINGER: ♪ Freighter man,
freighter man ♪

11:08.670 --> 11:12.636
♪ Which way's the freighter
gonna run tonight? ♪

11:12.636 --> 11:15.976
♪ Take me down
to Jacksonville ♪

11:15.976 --> 11:19.900
♪ Or just leave me be
wherever it seems right ♪

11:19.900 --> 11:23.658
♪ Duncan and Jimmy
walk side by side ♪

11:23.658 --> 11:27.373
♪ Nobody walks between them ♪

11:27.373 --> 11:31.047
♪ Duncan and Jimmy
walk side by side ♪

11:31.047 --> 11:34.053
<i>[muffled music continues]</i>

11:34.053 --> 11:36.601
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:36.601 --> 11:39.607
<i>[music resumes normally]</i>

11:39.607 --> 11:43.238
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:43.238 --> 11:46.286
[phone ringing]

11:46.286 --> 11:47.873
‐ Abdi?
<i>ANNIE: My pills!</i>

11:47.873 --> 11:50.252
<i>The recipe‐‐</i>
<i>what did you give me?</i>

11:50.252 --> 11:52.381
‐ Who's this?
<i>ANNIE: Anne Ingalls!</i>

11:52.381 --> 11:53.843
It's your employee.

11:53.843 --> 11:56.306
<i>NADIA: Anne,</i>
<i>it's really not a good time.</i>

11:56.306 --> 11:58.603
‐ My pills, they're all wrong.

11:58.603 --> 12:02.068
Something is messed up.
Did you change the recipe?

12:02.068 --> 12:04.573
‐ I replaced one with generics,
but they're exactly the same.

12:04.573 --> 12:05.825
<i>ANNIE: Something's wrong!</i>

12:05.825 --> 12:08.497
<i>I'm having</i>
<i>visual hallucinations!</i>

12:08.497 --> 12:10.502
NADIA: If your symptoms
are getting worse,

12:10.502 --> 12:12.380
then come in
and I'll refer you.

12:12.380 --> 12:13.967
<i>Anne, I can't do this</i>
<i>right now.</i>

12:13.967 --> 12:16.931
<i>I have a family emergency.</i>
<i>I'll be in contact.</i>

12:16.931 --> 12:19.477
‐ [breathing heavily]

12:19.477 --> 12:22.609
[muffled chatter]

12:22.609 --> 12:25.740
VERA: Who knows how many bodies
are at the bottom of this lake?

12:27.076 --> 12:29.163
TIMOTHY:
Vera knows all about bodies.

12:29.163 --> 12:32.169
Her dad was in Shawshank.
VERA: He was set up, okay?

12:32.169 --> 12:33.589
And then they shut down
the prison

12:33.589 --> 12:34.967
and he was sent to Ohio.

12:34.967 --> 12:37.179
Stop dishing
all my family trauma.

12:37.179 --> 12:38.599
At least
my dad doesn't beat me.

12:38.599 --> 12:40.102
‐ He isn't available
to beat you...

12:40.102 --> 12:41.981
VERA: Okay, whatever.
‐ He's in a fucking supermax.

12:41.981 --> 12:44.945
‐ Guys, less family therapy,
more trawling for dead bodies.

12:44.945 --> 12:48.452
‐ Well, Chance doesn't have
to worry about parents
because Chance is emancipated.

12:48.452 --> 12:50.707
‐ "Emancipated"?
Like, free?

12:50.707 --> 12:52.919
‐ As a fucking bird.
VERA: Language.

12:52.919 --> 12:55.299
Joy's mom hates
those F‐bombs, Chance.

12:55.299 --> 12:56.886
TIMOTHY: Vera.

12:56.886 --> 12:58.681
VERA: What would happen,
do you think,
if you just dropped one?

12:58.681 --> 13:01.227
A big old "fuck"
right in her lap.

13:01.227 --> 13:02.606
JOY:
It wouldn't be good, I think.

13:02.606 --> 13:04.818
I‐‐I know 'cause...
[both laugh]

13:04.818 --> 13:06.530
She has all these rules
to protect me,

13:06.530 --> 13:09.828
and even if they're dumb
or stupid, you know,

13:09.828 --> 13:11.456
I know why she's that way.

13:11.456 --> 13:14.295
And‐‐and, I mean, who cares

13:14.295 --> 13:17.051
if I can't say
some stupid word?

13:17.051 --> 13:20.057
Who cares if I can't say
some dumb...

13:20.057 --> 13:21.685
fucking word?

13:21.685 --> 13:24.817
Who cares if
I can't say "fuck"?

13:24.817 --> 13:27.656
VERA: Whoa‐‐whoa, there.
‐ Fuck, fuckity‐fuck.

13:27.656 --> 13:28.783
Fuckle‐fuck!
Fuck!

13:28.783 --> 13:31.789
[all laughing]

13:34.335 --> 13:36.966
W‐what?
[laughs]

13:36.966 --> 13:39.428
VERA:
How are those brownies, Crash?

13:39.428 --> 13:40.682
[laughs]
‐ Are‐‐are they...

13:40.682 --> 13:42.602
[stammers]
Oh.

13:42.602 --> 13:44.480
Was there something in those?
‐ Oh, I don't know.

13:44.480 --> 13:46.902
CHANCE: Breathe.
I hardly put any in there.

13:46.902 --> 13:49.323
‐ Is the talking normal?
TIMOTHY: Hilarious.

13:49.323 --> 13:50.577
VERA: So funny.

13:50.577 --> 13:52.622
CHANCE: Hey, uh, Timothy,
can you row a little bit?

13:52.622 --> 13:54.208
My arms are
getting really tired.

13:54.208 --> 13:55.920
TIMOTHY: Yep, gotcha.

13:55.920 --> 13:57.591
Oops!
VERA: Are you kidding?

13:57.591 --> 13:58.968
God!
CHANCE: What the fuck?

13:58.968 --> 14:00.805
VERA:
Well, I am not getting in.

14:00.805 --> 14:01.849
My asthma.
TIMOTHY: I can't reach it!

14:01.849 --> 14:04.020
CHANCE: Well...

14:04.020 --> 14:05.188
I threw it right to you.
‐ Aww, man.

14:05.188 --> 14:06.609
VERA: What are you‐‐
what is she doing?

14:06.609 --> 14:07.986
JOY: I'll get it.

14:07.986 --> 14:09.280
TIMOTHY: Do you know
how cold that is?

14:09.280 --> 14:11.619
[all laughing, chattering]

14:11.619 --> 14:14.373
<i>[eerie music]</i>

14:14.373 --> 14:17.379
[muffled, inaudible chatter]

14:17.379 --> 14:19.091
[rhythmic muffled whirring]

14:19.091 --> 14:20.595
[eerie groaning]

14:20.595 --> 14:23.559
[distorted splashing]

14:23.559 --> 14:26.314
JOY: There's a weird sound
down there.

14:26.314 --> 14:28.318
CHANCE: How many brownies
did you eat?

14:31.157 --> 14:32.994
<i>VERA: Hey, Chance, stop!</i>

14:32.994 --> 14:34.706
Stop!
CHANCE: It's too fast for you.

14:34.706 --> 14:35.833
VERA: Stop it!

14:35.833 --> 14:37.169
Oh, my God,
you're so annoying!

14:37.169 --> 14:39.173
CHANCE: I almost fell!
‐ Good.

14:39.173 --> 14:40.551
CHANCE: Ooh!
‐ Stop!

14:40.551 --> 14:42.429
‐ Hey, you know what?
You're a fucking mermaid.

14:42.429 --> 14:43.808
JOY: [laughs]
Thanks.

14:43.808 --> 14:46.104
VERA: Well, mermaids
are monsters, actually.

14:46.104 --> 14:47.857
Disney lies, so‐‐

14:47.857 --> 14:49.695
And I'm giving you swim lessons
for your birthday.

14:49.695 --> 14:50.947
‐ No, you're not.
VERA: Yeah, I am.

14:50.947 --> 14:52.241
‐ No‐‐

14:52.241 --> 14:53.451
VERA: Well, too bad,
'cause I'm giving you‐‐

14:53.451 --> 14:55.038
Stop!
‐ [laughs]

14:55.038 --> 14:56.792
See you later.
VERA: See ya.

14:56.792 --> 14:58.253
‐ Peace.

14:58.253 --> 14:59.756
‐ Bye, Joy.

14:59.756 --> 15:02.595
JOY: Bye.

15:02.595 --> 15:05.392
‐ That was, um...

15:05.392 --> 15:07.897
pretty badass...

15:07.897 --> 15:09.985
especially while high
for the first time.

15:09.985 --> 15:12.281
[both laugh]
JOY: Yeah.

15:13.617 --> 15:16.205
CHANCE: [sighs]

15:16.205 --> 15:19.003
Do you feel normal again?

15:19.003 --> 15:20.297
‐ Think so.

15:20.297 --> 15:22.886
‐ Ah, that's too bad.

15:22.886 --> 15:25.892
[birds chirping]

15:34.033 --> 15:37.039
<i>[quiet, tender music]</i>

15:37.039 --> 15:39.376
[phone chirps]

15:39.376 --> 15:43.928
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:43.928 --> 15:46.390
Keep your phone on.

15:46.390 --> 15:53.113
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:53.113 --> 15:56.578
[door opens]

15:56.578 --> 15:58.624
[door shuts]

15:58.624 --> 16:04.761
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:10.147 --> 16:12.401
JOY: Mom, I'm sorry‐‐

16:16.660 --> 16:19.248
I was, uh...

16:19.248 --> 16:22.881
I was just at the gas station
getting some food.

16:25.468 --> 16:28.141
What is all this?

16:34.654 --> 16:37.492
I'll get your pills.

16:37.492 --> 16:39.539
‐ No.

16:42.252 --> 16:44.507
No, I think she poisoned me.

16:47.847 --> 16:49.935
JOY: What?

16:49.935 --> 16:52.397
‐ The doctor...

16:52.397 --> 16:54.485
at the clinic.

16:56.113 --> 16:58.619
The one you like so much.

17:00.413 --> 17:03.044
Her pills made me worse,
not better.

17:04.506 --> 17:06.677
They made me do a bad thing.

17:09.348 --> 17:11.770
‐ What bad thing?

17:16.445 --> 17:18.784
‐ When I say this...

17:20.245 --> 17:22.875
You have to hear me out.

17:24.796 --> 17:27.802
I killed a man.

17:27.802 --> 17:30.683
<i>[tense music]</i>

17:30.683 --> 17:33.021
‐ What?

17:33.021 --> 17:34.148
‐ The dirty bird

17:34.148 --> 17:37.487
with the dirty look
on his face.

17:37.487 --> 17:40.076
‐ Ace Merrill?

17:40.076 --> 17:42.372
‐ He came here...

17:42.372 --> 17:45.713
and he threatened you.

17:45.713 --> 17:48.761
Threatened us both...

17:48.761 --> 17:52.267
in the vilest language, Joy.

17:52.267 --> 17:55.440
So...

17:55.440 --> 17:57.779
I ended him...

17:57.779 --> 18:00.200
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:00.200 --> 18:02.287
Right there.

18:02.287 --> 18:04.041
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:04.041 --> 18:05.836
But then I cleaned it up
so good

18:05.836 --> 18:08.091
I can't find a trace of it.

18:08.091 --> 18:11.598
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:11.598 --> 18:13.393
Not a single speck of him,

18:13.393 --> 18:16.023
but I swear...

18:16.023 --> 18:17.527
I did it.

18:17.527 --> 18:20.448
And then I took him to the pit
and I threw him in the hole.

18:20.448 --> 18:22.202
JOY: Mom, uh‐‐

18:22.202 --> 18:25.333
ANNIE: That's not even
the worst of it,

18:25.333 --> 18:28.716
because he came back.

18:28.716 --> 18:31.513
That Ace...

18:31.513 --> 18:33.015
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:33.015 --> 18:34.769
After.

18:34.769 --> 18:36.732
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:36.732 --> 18:38.025
‐ "After"?

18:38.025 --> 18:39.988
ANNIE: After I...

18:39.988 --> 18:42.618
I saw him.

18:42.618 --> 18:45.833
‐ I‐‐I don't understand.

18:45.833 --> 18:48.505
‐ Me neither,
but I killed him, Joy.

18:48.505 --> 18:50.968
I killed him.

18:50.968 --> 18:53.222
[both breathing heavily]

18:53.222 --> 19:00.236
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:28.752 --> 19:31.633
All I know...

19:31.633 --> 19:34.597
is I try so hard
to be there for you.

19:34.597 --> 19:37.770
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:37.770 --> 19:40.776
To be my best self
and not the other one.

19:40.776 --> 19:43.574
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:43.574 --> 19:46.705
‐ Mom...

19:46.705 --> 19:48.625
y‐you must have...

19:48.625 --> 19:51.297
‐ What?

19:51.297 --> 19:53.594
Imagined it?

19:53.594 --> 19:56.140
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:56.140 --> 19:59.396
I killed that man,

19:59.396 --> 20:02.862
and then he came back.

20:02.862 --> 20:05.659
And he'll come again...

20:05.659 --> 20:07.955
to finish it.

20:07.955 --> 20:09.709
‐ Mom...

20:09.709 --> 20:12.088
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:12.088 --> 20:14.802
‐ You believe me...

20:14.802 --> 20:17.140
don't you?

20:17.140 --> 20:24.154
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:28.245 --> 20:31.251
[breathing shakily]

20:31.251 --> 20:33.172
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:33.172 --> 20:36.136
[weeping softly]

20:36.136 --> 20:38.600
JOY: I love you, Mom.
ANNIE: [grunts]

20:38.600 --> 20:40.269
<i>[melancholy music]</i>

20:40.269 --> 20:43.150
[groans softly]

20:43.150 --> 20:44.946
No...

20:44.946 --> 20:47.576
No, no, Joy, we said...

20:47.576 --> 20:51.125
[stammers]
For emergencies.

20:51.125 --> 20:53.630
No...
JOY: I love you, Mom.

20:53.630 --> 20:55.843
ANNIE: Joy, no, no.

20:55.843 --> 20:58.472
[body thuds]

20:58.472 --> 21:01.771
[weeping]
They're for emergencies...

21:05.069 --> 21:07.198
[bell tolling]

21:07.198 --> 21:10.204
[indistinct chatter]

21:10.204 --> 21:12.008
[engines rumbling]
NADIA: [speaking Somali]

21:13.398 --> 21:14.298
ABDI: [speaking Somali]

21:32.875 --> 21:35.506
‐ Eh?
‐ Mm‐hmm.

21:43.437 --> 21:46.318
[birds chirping]

21:50.243 --> 21:52.873
[passing engines rumbling]

22:02.768 --> 22:04.730
<i>NURSE:</i>
<i>Wheelchair to admitting.</i>

22:04.730 --> 22:07.193
<i>Wheelchair to admitting.</i>

22:07.193 --> 22:10.199
<i>[eerie music]</i>

22:10.199 --> 22:17.172
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:21.639 --> 22:24.311
[door latch clicks]

22:24.311 --> 22:31.325
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:33.622 --> 22:36.335
‐ You piece of shit.

22:36.335 --> 22:38.422
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:38.422 --> 22:40.176
‐ Hello, Pop.

22:40.176 --> 22:42.765
‐ Where the fuck you been?

22:42.765 --> 22:44.392
[monitor beeping steadily]

22:44.392 --> 22:46.271
‐ Derry.

22:46.271 --> 22:48.693
‐ You're a murderer now?

22:48.693 --> 22:50.948
Your own fucking family?

22:50.948 --> 22:54.538
Trying to burn
Nadia's house down.

22:54.538 --> 22:56.458
The hell is wrong with you?

22:56.458 --> 22:58.588
‐ That was a mistake.

22:58.588 --> 22:59.674
‐ "Mistake"?

22:59.674 --> 23:01.385
Your whole goddamn life's
a mistake.

23:01.385 --> 23:02.428
JAMAL: All right,
stay down, Pop.

23:02.428 --> 23:04.725
ACE: My whole life, yes.

23:04.725 --> 23:06.938
‐ The fuck
you talking like that for?

23:06.938 --> 23:09.902
Thought you were dead,
you fucking moron!

23:09.902 --> 23:11.781
JAMAL: Take it easy‐‐
‐ The fuck out of here!

23:11.781 --> 23:13.868
JAMAL: Take it easy,
take it easy.

23:13.868 --> 23:15.914
[door slams]

23:15.914 --> 23:22.928
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:29.525 --> 23:31.236
<i>[dramatic opera music]</i>

23:31.236 --> 23:34.242
SINGER:
[singing in foreign language]

23:34.242 --> 23:41.214
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:45.891 --> 23:48.897
[engine revving]

23:48.897 --> 23:51.736
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:51.736 --> 23:54.742
[sirens wailing]

23:54.742 --> 23:57.623
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:57.623 --> 24:00.629
[engine revving]

24:00.629 --> 24:06.056
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:06.056 --> 24:08.520
<i>ANDERSEN: [over PA]</i>
<i>Pull over, asshole.</i>

24:08.520 --> 24:11.526
[sirens wailing]

24:11.526 --> 24:14.532
[thunder rumbles]

24:15.575 --> 24:18.581
<i>Hey, fuck nuts,</i>
<i>get out of the car.</i>

24:18.581 --> 24:21.294
<i>[song continues over radio]</i>

24:21.294 --> 24:24.259
<i>[radio chatter]</i>

24:24.259 --> 24:26.556
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:26.556 --> 24:30.062
[thunder crashes]

24:30.062 --> 24:32.191
Right now, asshole!

24:32.191 --> 24:34.905
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:34.905 --> 24:37.243
Hey!

24:37.243 --> 24:40.291
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:42.963 --> 24:45.969
<i>[tense music]</i>

24:45.969 --> 24:52.983
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:11.394 --> 25:14.400
‐ [breathing heavily]

25:27.678 --> 25:29.974
[phone buzzes]

25:49.597 --> 25:52.101
<i>[message notification]</i>

25:53.563 --> 25:55.650
<i>[phone buzzes]</i>

25:57.028 --> 25:59.575
‐ [breathing shakily]

25:59.575 --> 26:01.829
ANNIE: Joy.

26:01.829 --> 26:04.500
[stammers, grunts]

26:04.500 --> 26:07.256
Come‐‐come untie me.

26:08.801 --> 26:11.724
Little love, please.

26:11.724 --> 26:13.477
[phone buzzes]

26:14.647 --> 26:17.944
Please, Joy.

26:19.489 --> 26:22.495
[headboard thumping]

26:24.123 --> 26:26.545
Little love.
‐ [sighs]

26:26.545 --> 26:28.340
Are you ready?

26:31.388 --> 26:33.601
‐ For what?

26:37.818 --> 26:39.780
‐ Your pills.

26:39.780 --> 26:44.205
‐ When we made this‐‐
this plan, you and I...

26:45.499 --> 26:49.340
If for ever I had‐‐
I had a spell...

26:49.340 --> 26:53.641
The thing is, little love,
we never talked enough

26:53.641 --> 26:57.774
about what a genuine emergency
might look like.

26:57.774 --> 26:59.653
‐ You said you killed a man.

27:01.741 --> 27:03.285
‐ Yes.

27:03.285 --> 27:06.709
‐ You said the man you killed
came back to life to kill us.

27:06.709 --> 27:08.378
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:08.378 --> 27:12.554
It's an emergency
when you see things
that aren't there, Mom.

27:12.554 --> 27:14.683
‐ Well, see, I‐‐

27:14.683 --> 27:16.520
‐ Take your pills.

27:16.520 --> 27:18.900
‐ They aren't the right pills.

27:18.900 --> 27:21.029
‐ They are.
I checked.

27:21.029 --> 27:24.828
It's the right recipe.
40, 20, 10.

27:24.828 --> 27:26.624
ANNIE: Don't you see, Joy?

27:26.624 --> 27:29.630
‐ The plan is‐‐is that
I don't let you out
until you take your pills.

27:29.630 --> 27:33.596
‐ The medicine is wrong
so the plan is off, Joy!

27:33.596 --> 27:36.476
‐ That's what you said
you'd say when we made‐‐

27:36.476 --> 27:40.067
‐ Joy, jiminy Christmas!

27:40.067 --> 27:41.904
‐ If you need water.

27:41.904 --> 27:44.033
‐ [breathing heavily]

27:44.033 --> 27:45.912
Wait!

27:45.912 --> 27:50.630
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:50.630 --> 27:53.803
I'll take them.

27:53.803 --> 27:56.850
Just give them to me.
I'll take them.

27:56.850 --> 28:00.440
[sighs]
Get it over with.

28:00.440 --> 28:02.696
JOY: Okay.

28:02.696 --> 28:05.702
[pills rattling]

28:11.672 --> 28:14.135
[insect chirps]

28:25.365 --> 28:27.537
Open.

28:37.974 --> 28:40.772
ANNIE: Okay, little love.

28:40.772 --> 28:42.191
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:42.191 --> 28:44.362
Untie me now.

28:44.362 --> 28:46.366
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:46.366 --> 28:48.244
‐ Not yet, Mama.

28:48.244 --> 28:50.457
You're not ready.

28:50.457 --> 28:52.629
[fabric rustles
and chair creaks]

28:52.629 --> 28:54.966
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:54.966 --> 28:57.388
You didn't kill anyone.

28:57.388 --> 28:59.810
Ace Merrill is still alive.

28:59.810 --> 29:02.649
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:02.649 --> 29:04.861
‐ Sweetie...

29:04.861 --> 29:10.330
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:10.330 --> 29:12.919
JOY: Let me know
if you need the bedpan.

29:12.919 --> 29:15.883
[retreating footsteps]

29:15.883 --> 29:18.973
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:18.973 --> 29:21.394
[door shuts]

29:21.394 --> 29:25.110
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:25.110 --> 29:28.116
[mice squeaking]

29:28.116 --> 29:32.124
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:32.124 --> 29:33.961
ANNIE: [spits]

29:33.961 --> 29:35.923
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:35.923 --> 29:38.929
[engine rumbling]

29:47.196 --> 29:49.701
‐ No, Kevin, no, no.

29:49.701 --> 29:51.955
Just because I made more money
than you last year‐‐

29:51.955 --> 29:55.420
no, that doesn't mean
that child support flip‐flops.

29:55.420 --> 29:57.884
Uh‐huh, yeah.

29:57.884 --> 29:59.136
Mm‐hmm.

29:59.136 --> 30:00.347
[gasps]
Oh!

30:00.347 --> 30:03.353
[stammers, laughs]
Oh, excuse me.

30:03.353 --> 30:04.523
Uh...
[clears throat]

30:04.523 --> 30:06.985
Valerie Blount,
Blount Real Estate.

30:06.985 --> 30:08.196
‐ John Merrill.

30:08.196 --> 30:11.703
‐ "John" as in, uh,
Ace Merrill?

30:11.703 --> 30:13.541
‐ Mm‐hmm.

30:13.541 --> 30:16.672
‐ Uh, shall we?

30:19.260 --> 30:22.140
Uh, you know,
the house was originally built

30:22.140 --> 30:24.980
by, uh, a millionaire,
Hubie Marsten,

30:24.980 --> 30:26.148
back in the '20s.

30:26.148 --> 30:29.154
‐ A gangster
who practiced black magic.

30:29.154 --> 30:31.660
Lost his mind, shot his wife,
hanged himself.

30:31.660 --> 30:34.164
‐ Mm, can't fool the locals.

30:34.164 --> 30:35.292
[keys jingling]

30:35.292 --> 30:36.795
ACE: Do you have children?

30:36.795 --> 30:38.549
‐ Uh...
[laughs]

30:38.549 --> 30:40.343
Um, yes.

30:40.343 --> 30:43.433
One, middle school.

30:43.433 --> 30:45.730
Pretty much takes care
of himself these days.

30:45.730 --> 30:49.320
‐ But you're still able
to have children...

30:49.320 --> 30:51.032
right?

30:51.032 --> 30:52.619
VALERIE: Uh‐huh.

30:52.619 --> 30:54.330
That's a...
[laughs]

30:54.330 --> 30:56.585
That is a funny question.

30:56.585 --> 31:00.133
[door creaks, opens]

31:00.133 --> 31:01.970
Uh...

31:05.728 --> 31:08.149
Oh, this shouldn't be here.

31:10.487 --> 31:13.159
Hello?

31:13.159 --> 31:15.790
Um...

31:15.790 --> 31:17.961
Hello?

31:19.338 --> 31:22.260
Uh, can you just wait one sec?

31:27.229 --> 31:29.859
[muffled thud, creak]

31:31.487 --> 31:32.865
[muffled thud]

31:32.865 --> 31:34.995
Is somebody here?

31:34.995 --> 31:37.374
[muffled thud]

31:49.899 --> 31:52.070
<i>[sinister music]</i>

31:52.070 --> 31:54.659
[gasps]
ANDERSEN: [gasps, coughs]

31:54.659 --> 31:57.247
‐ [gasps]
Oh...

31:57.247 --> 31:58.751
[gasps]

31:58.751 --> 32:01.172
ANDERSON: [hollers, groans]
VALERIE: [gasps, exclaims]

32:01.172 --> 32:04.804
‐ [panting, coughing]

32:04.804 --> 32:08.019
The car...
[wheezing]

32:08.019 --> 32:11.067
‐ Ugh‐‐oh!
[gasps, screams]

32:11.067 --> 32:12.904
Oh, my God!

32:16.160 --> 32:18.372
[pills rattling]

32:18.372 --> 32:21.337
[thunder rumbling]

32:21.337 --> 32:24.343
<i>[tense music]</i>

32:24.343 --> 32:31.357
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:33.027 --> 32:35.490
‐ [gasps]
Joy!

32:35.490 --> 32:36.993
[body thuds]

32:36.993 --> 32:40.041
[whimpering, choking]

32:40.041 --> 32:44.759
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:44.759 --> 32:47.765
[gasping]

32:47.765 --> 32:54.779
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:25.298 --> 33:28.304
[thunder crashes]

33:31.352 --> 33:35.945
‐ "Ian held her stiffening body
as Orpheo tumbled on, heedless,

33:35.945 --> 33:38.491
"through the lashing
bracken of Shadow Wood

33:38.491 --> 33:41.080
"as the adder's venom
worked its way deeper,

33:41.080 --> 33:43.919
black tendrils reaching
for her heart."

33:47.175 --> 33:50.181
It's late.

33:50.181 --> 33:52.269
‐ [sighs]

33:52.269 --> 33:55.651
You know, I used to read
to my father.

33:55.651 --> 33:58.239
Tried to, anyway.

33:58.239 --> 34:01.245
I'd always jumble up the words.

34:01.245 --> 34:04.251
[rain pattering]

34:04.251 --> 34:05.921
JOY: Mom?

34:07.591 --> 34:09.804
ANNIE: Yes?

34:14.313 --> 34:17.444
‐ What's in that?
The lockbox.

34:18.947 --> 34:20.868
‐ Just papers.

34:20.868 --> 34:22.580
[thunder rumbles]

34:22.580 --> 34:25.669
‐ Show me.

34:25.669 --> 34:29.802
‐ Nothing but nonsense
in there, Joy, honestly.

34:29.802 --> 34:32.015
‐ Then why does it need
a big lock,

34:32.015 --> 34:34.854
and why can't I
just look inside?

34:35.939 --> 34:38.945
[alarm beeping]

34:44.456 --> 34:46.586
[alarm stops]

34:48.757 --> 34:50.969
[pills rattle]

35:06.584 --> 35:08.421
‐ I feel so much better,
little love.

35:08.421 --> 35:10.466
Thank you...

35:10.466 --> 35:12.680
for everything.

35:12.680 --> 35:16.145
[thunder rumbling]

35:16.145 --> 35:19.151
[pills rattle]

35:19.151 --> 35:21.740
[shuffling footsteps]

35:26.457 --> 35:29.463
[thunder rumbling]

35:38.439 --> 35:41.445
[rain pattering]

35:55.516 --> 35:58.522
[grunting softly]

35:59.732 --> 36:01.736
<i>[tense music]</i>

36:01.736 --> 36:03.782
[gasps]

36:03.782 --> 36:10.796
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:12.215 --> 36:15.221
[thunder rumbles]

36:15.221 --> 36:16.933
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:16.933 --> 36:19.396
[grunts]

36:19.396 --> 36:21.441
[grunting]

36:21.441 --> 36:23.572
[glass shatters]

36:23.572 --> 36:26.578
[glass scraping
and thunder crashes]

36:26.578 --> 36:29.584
[door rattling]

36:29.584 --> 36:36.598
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:44.154 --> 36:47.493
‐ If you're really
better, Mom...

36:47.493 --> 36:49.707
tell the truth.

36:49.707 --> 36:51.335
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:51.335 --> 36:54.800
‐ About what?

36:54.800 --> 36:56.679
‐ Everything.

36:56.679 --> 36:59.852
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:59.852 --> 37:02.357
Now, Mom.

37:02.357 --> 37:04.277
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:04.277 --> 37:06.658
[thunder rumbles]

37:06.658 --> 37:10.289
What are we running from?

37:10.289 --> 37:11.834
You're not getting out
of that bed

37:11.834 --> 37:14.632
until you tell me the truth.

37:14.632 --> 37:18.138
[thunder rumbles]

37:18.138 --> 37:21.144
[retreating footsteps]

37:21.144 --> 37:23.608
‐ He didn't want you.

37:26.990 --> 37:29.745
Your father,
he didn't want you.

37:34.129 --> 37:36.216
And I did...

37:36.216 --> 37:38.847
so I took you and I ran.

37:38.847 --> 37:42.311
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:42.311 --> 37:44.817
I didn't expect the police
to understand what he was,

37:44.817 --> 37:48.032
and lo and behold,
they did not.

37:48.032 --> 37:52.081
I told a lot of lies
to a lot of people...

37:52.081 --> 37:56.006
but I told you only one...

37:56.006 --> 37:58.385
because I didn't want you
to be afraid.

37:58.385 --> 38:00.139
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:00.139 --> 38:03.563
‐ Why would I be afraid?

38:03.563 --> 38:06.569
‐ Because he's coming
for us now.

38:06.569 --> 38:08.113
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:08.113 --> 38:11.203
He's a very bad man, Joy,

38:11.203 --> 38:13.750
and he's not gonna stop.

38:13.750 --> 38:15.419
He'll never stop.

38:15.419 --> 38:18.258
That's why
you have to untie me‐‐

38:18.258 --> 38:21.139
so I can protect you!

38:21.139 --> 38:24.104
‐ You said Dad was a hero.

38:24.104 --> 38:25.899
That he died in a war.

38:25.899 --> 38:27.611
‐ Yes.

38:27.611 --> 38:29.322
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:29.322 --> 38:31.953
It was just better.

38:31.953 --> 38:34.708
It was better, Joy,
i‐if you were running

38:34.708 --> 38:37.004
towards the Laughing Place
and not away from‐‐

38:37.004 --> 38:39.802
‐ You said
lying is the worst thing

38:39.802 --> 38:41.597
that people who
love each other can do.

38:41.597 --> 38:43.935
‐ I know, I did,
and‐‐and it is.

38:43.935 --> 38:46.231
‐ How could you?

38:46.231 --> 38:48.068
ANNIE: Everything I do

38:48.068 --> 38:52.703
is because I believe
in a better world, Joy.

38:52.703 --> 38:56.376
And that takes work, Joy.

38:56.376 --> 38:57.796
Hard work.

38:57.796 --> 38:59.132
Sometimes when we're
on the road,

38:59.132 --> 39:01.178
we're rounding a cloverleaf,
I look out the window

39:01.178 --> 39:04.602
and I look at all that dirt
and that grit‐‐

39:04.602 --> 39:06.898
the ugliness going by
and I think,

39:06.898 --> 39:09.485
"Well, Annie,
you're wasting your time."

39:09.485 --> 39:13.828
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:13.828 --> 39:15.916
[stammers]

39:15.916 --> 39:17.335
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:17.335 --> 39:19.798
I look at you...
[laughs]

39:19.798 --> 39:22.303
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:22.303 --> 39:25.894
And the sun just...

39:25.894 --> 39:28.775
rises.
[laughs, sniffles]

39:28.775 --> 39:30.486
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:30.486 --> 39:33.826
You are my better world, Joy.

39:33.826 --> 39:37.124
[weeping softly]

39:37.124 --> 39:40.715
And, yes,
I've done bad for you...

39:40.715 --> 39:42.093
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:42.093 --> 39:44.013
And I'll do it again.

39:44.013 --> 39:46.393
I will do the doggone worst

39:46.393 --> 39:48.731
to protect you
from the monsters,

39:48.731 --> 39:51.988
and I'll feel
just fine about it.

39:51.988 --> 39:53.741
I won't give them
the satisfaction

39:53.741 --> 39:56.664
of a single regret...
[sniffles]

39:56.664 --> 40:01.047
Because the only thing
that matters is you.

40:01.047 --> 40:02.466
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:02.466 --> 40:05.765
My‐‐my world.

40:05.765 --> 40:08.312
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:08.312 --> 40:11.359
My little world.
[weeping softly]

40:11.359 --> 40:18.373
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:22.883 --> 40:25.847
<i>[tense music]</i>

40:25.847 --> 40:28.519
[stammers]
Joy...

40:28.519 --> 40:35.533
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:38.413 --> 40:42.213
‐ You didn't take your pills!
‐ You listen to me.

40:42.213 --> 40:45.260
You listen very carefully‐‐
‐ You lied again!

40:45.260 --> 40:46.429
‐ No.

40:46.429 --> 40:47.557
[knocking on door]

40:47.557 --> 40:49.603
Don't‐‐don't answer.

40:49.603 --> 40:52.024
Please, don't answer.
That could be him.

40:52.024 --> 40:54.530
‐ "Him" who?
Dad?

40:54.530 --> 40:57.744
Ace Merrill?
You don't even know, do you?

40:57.744 --> 41:00.917
They‐‐they're all just monsters
out to get us!

41:00.917 --> 41:03.130
ANNIE: You're fudging right
they are!

41:03.130 --> 41:04.925
[door slams]

41:04.925 --> 41:07.054
[panting]

41:07.054 --> 41:09.977
[grunting]

41:09.977 --> 41:15.947
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:15.947 --> 41:19.538
[grunting, panting]

41:19.538 --> 41:26.552
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:26.552 --> 41:29.558
[knocking continues]

41:29.558 --> 41:36.572
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:37.824 --> 41:40.663
[grunting]

41:40.663 --> 41:42.667
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:42.667 --> 41:44.462
[strains]

41:44.462 --> 41:47.426
[grunts]
[panting]

41:47.426 --> 41:49.556
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:49.556 --> 41:50.892
[crunch]

41:50.892 --> 41:53.355
[gasps, groans]

41:53.355 --> 41:56.361
[whimpering]

41:56.361 --> 41:58.198
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:58.198 --> 42:01.204
[knocking continues]

42:01.204 --> 42:08.218
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:16.192 --> 42:19.073
‐ Is your mom here?

42:19.073 --> 42:21.745
JOY: She's... sick.

42:21.745 --> 42:24.292
She can't come to the door
right now.

42:24.292 --> 42:26.337
[rain pattering]

42:26.337 --> 42:27.799
‐ But everything's okay?

42:27.799 --> 42:29.678
‐ Sure.

42:29.678 --> 42:31.515
‐ It's just that she called me
very upset

42:31.515 --> 42:33.476
and... didn't show up for work.

42:33.476 --> 42:35.355
‐ It‐‐it was the stomach bug,

42:35.355 --> 42:37.902
but... she's all better now.

42:37.902 --> 42:41.075
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:41.075 --> 42:44.081
‐ [groaning]

42:44.081 --> 42:47.672
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:47.672 --> 42:49.300
[strains]

42:49.300 --> 42:52.014
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:52.014 --> 42:55.395
[groaning]

42:55.395 --> 42:57.609
‐ Are you sure
you're okay, Joy?

42:57.609 --> 43:01.867
Your mom sounded like
she was having
some pretty serious symptoms.

43:01.867 --> 43:05.750
‐ You should have sent her
to‐‐to a head doctor.

43:05.750 --> 43:08.463
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:08.463 --> 43:11.219
You don't know anything
about her.

43:11.219 --> 43:13.098
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

43:13.098 --> 43:14.350
[crunch]

43:14.350 --> 43:15.895
[gasps, cries out]

43:15.895 --> 43:18.901
[panting]

43:18.901 --> 43:25.915
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:29.213 --> 43:31.050
JOY: Mom!

43:31.050 --> 43:32.804
Mom!

43:32.804 --> 43:35.518
Mom.

43:35.518 --> 43:37.772
ANNIE: [hollers]

43:37.772 --> 43:39.901
Joy, Joy, Joy, Joy!

43:39.901 --> 43:42.574
Oh, dear God.
Joy, I didn't mean‐‐

43:42.574 --> 43:44.578
No, no, Joy!

43:44.578 --> 43:46.582
Joy, Joy, Joy!

43:46.582 --> 43:48.544
I‐‐I didn't mean...

43:48.544 --> 43:50.673
[door slams]

43:50.673 --> 43:53.679
[panting]

43:53.679 --> 44:00.693
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:06.538 --> 44:09.544
[thunder rumbling]

44:09.544 --> 44:12.299
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:12.299 --> 44:14.846
Joy!

44:14.846 --> 44:18.521
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:18.521 --> 44:20.817
Joy, where are you?

44:20.817 --> 44:27.831
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:28.916 --> 44:32.297
[hyperventilating]

44:34.511 --> 44:37.266
[panting]

44:43.069 --> 44:46.075
[door opens]
[thunder crashes]

44:46.075 --> 44:47.829
<i>[sinister music]</i>

44:47.829 --> 44:50.166
[door closes]
<i>[typewriter key clacks]</i>

44:50.166 --> 44:52.087
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:52.087 --> 44:55.093
[slow, heavy footsteps]

44:55.093 --> 45:02.107
<i>♪ ♪</i>

45:05.280 --> 45:08.286
[footsteps continue]

45:08.286 --> 45:15.258
<i>♪ ♪</i>

45:16.469 --> 45:18.473
[thunder rumbles]

45:18.473 --> 45:20.895
TALL MAN:
You know how this story ends.

45:20.895 --> 45:24.736
<i>♪ ♪</i>

45:24.736 --> 45:27.157
You're going to kill her.

45:27.157 --> 45:30.748
<i>♪ ♪</i>

45:30.748 --> 45:33.754
<i>[thunder rumbles]</i>

45:33.754 --> 45:36.760
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

45:36.760 --> 45:43.774
<i>♪ ♪</i>

46:52.035 --> 46:53.664
<i>‐ Bad Robot.</i>
